# {{context|psychology|lang=en}} The pattern of deriving adult [[sexual]] [[arousal]] from objects that one was exposed to as an infant. The [[fetish]] value often stems from tactile stimulation similar to that experienced by the infant before it could see well.
# {{context|psychology|lang=en}} In [[Freudian]] theory, the relation between bodily functions in early childhood and the later development of the sexual instinct. The infant's bodily function of simple hunger, to take a primary example, is at first attached solely to the act of suckling at mother's breast.

